Column Comment.0: UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as theprimary key for this row.
Column Comment.1: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.2: AIR DRLLING OBSERVATION NUMBER: The air drilling observation number usedfor the air drilling contractor record.
Column Comment.3: DEPTH OBSERVATOIN NUMBER: identifies the depth interval.
Column Comment.4: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.5: AIR GAS CODE: The type of fluid supplied by the drilling compressor. For example,the fluid can be Air or Gas.
Column Comment.6: BASE DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the bottom of the interval drilledwith compressed air/gas.
Column Comment.7: BASE DEPTH OUOM: Base depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.8: COMPRESSOR RATE VOLUME: Value for the rate of air/gas delivered by the aircompressor while drilling the interval. The rate is usually expressed in cubic feet perminute.
Column Comment.9: COMPRESSOR RATE VOLUME OUOM: Air/gas volume rate original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.10: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.11: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.12: MAXIMUM INTERVAL PRESSURE: Value for the maximum gauge pressurerecorded during air drilling of the interval.
Column Comment.13: MAXIMUM INTERVAL PRESSURE OUOM: Maximum gauge pressure original unit ofmeasure.
Column Comment.14: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL shouldbe created.
Column Comment.15: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.16: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.17: TOP DEPTH: Measured depth from the surface to the top of the interval drilled withcompressed air/gas.
Column Comment.18: TOP DEPTH OUOM: Top depth original unit of measure.
Column Comment.19: WATER INFLUX AMOUNT: Value for the amount of water entering the wellboreduring the air/gas drilling.
Column Comment.20: WATER INFLUX AMOUNT OUOM: Water influx original unit of measure.
Column Comment.21: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.22: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.23: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.24: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.25: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.26: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.27: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
